data.chText: 由于火势蔓延，须要立即采取行动。
data.enText: Prompt action was required as the fire spread.

data.chText: 见发票即付款，将不胜感激。
data.enText: Prompt payment of the invoice would be appreciated.
acting without delay; arriving at the right time

data.chText: 参加上述会议，请准时出席。
data.enText: Please be prompt when attending these meetings.
to make sb decide to do sth; to cause sth to happen

data.chText: 此次发现炸弹促使当局加强了安全工作。
data.enText: The discovery of the bomb prompted an increase in security.

data.chText: 他的讲话激起了人群中一男子的愤怒。
data.enText: His speech prompted an angry outburst from a man in the crowd.

data.chText: 对女儿婚期的操心使她消瘦不少。

data.hoverText: 动词+名词短语+带to的不定式

data.enText: The thought of her daughter's wedding day prompted her to lose some weight.

data.chText: 鼓励，提示，提醒（某人说话）
data.enText: to encourage sb to speak by asking them questions or suggesting words that they could say

data.chText: 她紧张得说不出话来，只好听人提示。
data.enText: She was too nervous to speak and had to be prompted.

data.chText: 这个程序在必要时将提醒你输入数据。
data.enText: The program will prompt you to enter data where required.

data.chText: “后来怎样了？”他鼓励对方继续说下去。

data.hoverText: 动词+名词短语+直接引语

data.enText: to follow the text of a play and remind the actors what the words are if they forget their lines
a word or words said to an actor, to remind them what to say next when they have forgotten
a sign on a computer screen that shows that the computer has finished doing sth and is ready for more instructions

data.chText: 会议将于十点钟准时开始。
data.enText: The meeting will begin at ten o'clock prompt.

means: 鼓励，提示，提醒(某人说话)

tr: (computer science) a symbol that appears on the computer screen to indicate that the computer is ready to receive a command
a cue given to a performer (usually the beginning of the next line to be spoken)
example: the audience could hear his prompting

tr: serve as the inciting cause of
example: She prompted me to call my relatives

tr: assist (somebody acting or reciting) by suggesting the next words of something forgotten or imperfectly learned

example: This moved me to sacrifice my career

tr: performed with little or no delay
example: an immediate reply to my letter

tr: according to schedule or without delay
ready and willing or quick to act
example: she is always prompt to help her friends

value.def: To prompt someone to do something means to make them decide to do it.

example.ex: Japan's recession has prompted consumers to cut back on buying cars...
example.tran: 日本经济的不景气使得消费者在购买车辆上减少了开支。

example.ex: The need for villagers to control their own destinies has prompted a new plan.
example.tran: 村民们想要掌握自己的命运，这促成了一项新的计划。

value.def: If you prompt someone when they stop speaking, you encourage or help them to continue. If you prompt an actor, you tell them what their next line is when they have forgotten what comes next.

example.ex: How exactly did he prompt her, Mr Markham?
example.tran: 确切地说，他是怎样提示她的，马卡姆先生？

example.ex: Her blushes were saved by a prompt from one of her hosts.
example.tran: 幸亏一位主持人提示，她才不至于尴尬脸红。

value.tran: 鼓励，提示（说话者）；给（演员）提词

value.def: A prompt action is done without any delay.

example.ex: It is not too late, but prompt action is needed.
example.tran: 现在还不算晚，但是需要立即采取行动。

example.ex: ...an inflammation of the eyeball which needs prompt treatment.
example.tran: 需要立即治疗的眼球炎症

value.tran: 迅速的；即刻的；立即的；及时的

value.def: If you are prompt to do something, you do it without delay or you are not late.

example.ex: You have been so prompt in carrying out all these commissions...
example.tran: 你执行所有这些命令可真够迅速的。

example.ex: We didn't worry because they were always so prompt with their rental payment.
example.tran: 我们不担心，因为他们交租金总是非常及时。
